    "causal_summary": "Two interrelated defects undermine memory quality in the generate-context.js pipeline. First, the extractors quality scorer applies up to +0.20 in bonuses for normal session activity, ensuring that five simultaneous soft failures still produce a score above 0.95 — making quality_score effectively binary and useless for discriminating good saves from bad ones. Second, the contamination filter is applied only to `observations` and `SUMMARY`, leaving `_JSON_SESSION_SUMMARY`, `_manualDecisions`, `recentContext`, and `technicalContext` completely uncleaned. This phase recalibrates the scorer and extends the filter to close both gaps.",
